---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const appName     = "Gratefuly";
const lastUpdated = "March 2026";
const contactEmail = "hello@wiplabs.app";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Privacy Policy — ${appName}`}
  description={`Privacy Policy for ${appName} by WIPLabs. Your journal stays private — everything stored on your device.`}
>
  <style>
    /* ── Hero ── */
    .policy-hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5C8A6E, #7EC8A0);
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .policy-hero .emoji { font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block; }
    .policy-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .policy-hero p {
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── Page body ── */
    .policy-page { padding: 4rem 0; max-width: 720px; }
    .meta { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .policy-page h2 {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .policy-page p  { color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .policy-page ul { color: var(--text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .policy-page a  { color: var(--accent); }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .back-link:hover { color: var(--text); }

    .highlight-box {
      background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .highlight-box p { margin: 0; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }

    hr { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 2rem 0; }
  </style>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="policy-hero">
    <span class="emoji">🌿</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Gratefuly — Daily Gratitude Journal</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="container">
    <div class="policy-page">
      <a href="/apps/gratefuly" class="back-link">← Back to {appName}</a>

      <p class="meta">{appName} · WIPLabs · Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <p>🔒 Gratefuly is built with privacy at its core. Your journal entries, photos, voice recordings, and videos are stored entirely on your device. We do not collect, transmit, or sell your personal data.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how WIPLabs ("we", "our", or "us") handles information
        when you use the {appName} mobile application. We are committed to protecting your
        privacy. Gratefuly does not require an account and stores all your data locally on
        your device.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>Gratefuly does not collect any personally identifiable information. All data you create is stored locally on your device and never transmitted to our servers. This includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Journal entries (text, mood, date)</li>
        <li>Photos attached to entries</li>
        <li>Voice recordings attached to entries</li>
        <li>Videos attached to entries</li>
        <li>Streak counts and app settings</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not have access to any of this data at any time.</p>

      <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
      <p>
        All your journal data is stored exclusively on your device using Apple's SwiftData
        framework. No data is uploaded to external servers. We do not require you to create
        an account or log in.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Analytics & Crash Reporting</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly does not use any third-party analytics or crash reporting tools.
        We do not track your usage patterns, session durations, or any behavioral data.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The free version of Gratefuly displays banner advertisements provided by Google AdMob.
        AdMob may use device identifiers to serve relevant ads. You can opt out of personalized
        advertising at any time in your device's Privacy settings under "Apple Advertising."
      </p>
      <p>Premium subscribers see no advertisements.</p>
      <p>
        For more information about Google's privacy practices, visit:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly offers optional premium subscriptions (Monthly, Yearly, Lifetime) processed
        entirely through Apple's App Store. We do not collect or store any payment information.
        All billing is handled by Apple.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Notifications</h2>
      <p>
        If you enable daily reminders, Gratefuly uses Apple's local notification system.
        These notifications are generated entirely on-device — no notification data is sent
        to our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>8. App Lock & Biometrics</h2>
      <p>
        If you enable the App Lock feature, your PIN is stored securely in Apple's Keychain
        on your device. Face ID and Touch ID authentication is handled entirely by Apple's
        LocalAuthentication framework. We never have access to your biometric data.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Photos, Camera & Microphone</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly requests access to your photo library only when you choose to add a photo
        or video to a journal entry. We only access the specific media you select — we do not
        scan or access your entire photo library.
      </p>
      <p>Microphone access is requested only when you choose to record a voice note.</p>

      <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Gratefuly is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has used
        the app, please contact us and we will take appropriate action.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Since all data is stored on your device, you have complete control over it. You can delete all app data at any time by deleting Gratefuly from your device.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — all data is on your device, always accessible to you</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong> — edit any entry directly in the app</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong> — delete individual entries or uninstall the app to remove all data</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on
        this page with an updated date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>
      </p>

      <hr />
      <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
        © 2026 WIP Labs · <a href="https://wiplabs.app">wiplabs.app</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>